Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Entry-Level Software Engineer, Wealth Management Engineering* role with *State Street*. I bring over three years of software engineering experience and a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University, and I am excited to help build full-stack capabilities that support portfolio and investment workflows for wealth managers.

In my recent software engineering roles, I have built the same technical foundation your team is hiring for: reliable APIs, web UIs, and release-focused engineering execution. At Sperse, I designed and delivered an MCP interaction layer spanning 1,000+ platform endpoints, defining resilient API contracts and workflow orchestration for high-stakes automated actions. I also shipped generative developer tooling that accelerated Java and JavaScript/TypeScript implementation for backend services and web UI integrations, while strengthening maintainability through peer code reviews. In parallel, I implemented test automation with unit and integration test coverage plus observability (Langfuse, LangSmith, tracing, structured logging) to catch failures early and improve software reliability in Agile delivery cycles.

At Qualitest, I contributed to a React and Spring Boot identity platform serving thousands of users across 30+ applications, building API and web UI features while supporting long-running data workflows with AWS Step Functions. I also designed a cloud-agnostic storage service with PostgreSQL and Redis that handled secure file operations across S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, and I helped define microservices boundaries that supported migration paths toward Azure and containerized runtimes (Docker, Kubernetes). This experience aligns well with your shift toward a scalable cloud-based architecture and event-driven engineering practices.

State Street's focus on integrated, scalable solutions that help investors manage risk and meet their objectives strongly resonates with me. I am equally motivated by your emphasis on data-driven innovation and collaborative engineering culture, and I would be excited to contribute to a team that keeps clients at the center while shipping dependable software.

I would value the opportunity to discuss how I can contribute to State Street's wealth management engineering mission. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

